    • getReferencedModePart

      public EntityValuedFetchable getReferencedModePart()
      Description copied from interface: FetchParent
      Whereas FetchParent.getReferencedMappingContainer() and FetchParent.getReferencedMappingType() return the referenced container type, this method returns the referenced part. E.g. for a many-to-one this method returns the ToOneAttributeMapping while FetchParent.getReferencedMappingContainer() and FetchParent.getReferencedMappingType() return the referenced EntityMappingType.
      Specified by:

      public FetchParent getFetchParent()
      Description copied from interface: Fetch
      Obtain the owner of this fetch. Ultimately used to identify the thing that "owns" this fetched navigable for the purpose of:

      * identifying the associated owner reference as we process the fetch * inject the fetched instance into the parent and potentially inject the parent reference into the fetched instance if it defines such injection (e.g. Parent)
